Summary: TESS has led to the discovery of hundreds of new planetary systems as well as new planets in previously known planet systems. Of particular note, are systems with known warm to temperate gas giant planets that have been found to have transiting companions. Included in the sample are known planet systems that will be first observed by TESS in Cycle 6.
